The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Tuesday, July 11, 2006

 Roads to avoid

 EM Bypass, Park Circus connector, AJC Bose Road flyover, Hospital Road, Red Road, 11 am onwards. Traffic will be diverted for the Prime Minister?s visit. 

 AIDS show

 Ek aur Munnabhai, a film to spread awareness about HIV/AIDS, will be launched at Hyatt Regency, 10 am.

 Interface

 Panel discussion on Arun Shourie?s book Falling Over Backwards (An essay against reservation and against judicial populism), at Crossword, 6 pm.

 Award

 Meritorious students will be awarded scholarships by Tata Steel Sports Club, at Tata Centre, 6 pm. 

 Exhibition

 Utsav 2006 at Ice Skating Rink, at 11 am.

 Heritage Festival, an exhibition of saris, at Mriganayani State Emporium, 10 am onwards.

 Monsoon Magic, an exhibition of handicrafts, at Academy of Fine Arts, 3 pm to 8 pm.

 Art beat

 Primal Force, an exhibition of paintings, at CIMA Gallery, 2 pm to 7 pm.

 An exhibition of photographs, Marie by Herself, at Akar Prakar, 3 pm to 8 pm.

 An exhibition of paintings, Art of Young Bengal, at Aakriti Art Gallery, 3 pm to 7 pm.

 From the City of Joy, an exhibition of paintings at Palladian Lounge, 11 am to 7 pm.




